parameters.name: SCET_UTC
parameters.description: Sample S/C event time UTC in YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sss format

parameters.name: MLST
parameters.description: Mars local time represented as decimal SOLs

parameters.name: TLST
parameters.description: Mars true local time for the current SOL represented as decimal SOLs

parameters.name: dB1_temp
parameters.description:
Temperature correction applied to IFG sensor 1 after the raw DN value has been converted 
                       to nT using the model sensor and electronics temperatures.

parameters.name: dB2_temp
parameters.description:
Temperature correction applied to IFG sensor 2 after the raw DN value has been converted 
                       to nT using the model sensor and electronics temperatures.

parameters.name: dB3_temp
parameters.description:
Temperature correction applied to IFG sensor 3 after the raw DN value has been converted 
                       to nT using the model sensor and electronics temperatures.

parameters.name: dB1_curr
parameters.description:
Solar array currents correction applied to IFG sensor 1 after the raw DN value has been converted 
                       to nT using the model solar arrat fixed and total currents.

parameters.name: dB2_curr
parameters.description:
Solar array currents correction applied to IFG sensor 2 after the raw DN value has been converted 
                       to nT using the model solar arrat fixed and total currents.

parameters.name: dB3_temp
parameters.description:
Solar array currents correction applied to IFG sensor 3 after the raw DN value has been converted 
                       to nT using the model solar arrat fixed and total currents.

parameters.name: modelST
parameters.description:
Value of the actual IFG sensor temperature [SensorT] when available, 
                       otherwise a MLST and UTC dependent model of the IFG sensor temperature [deg C]
                    	 derived from the measured values from selected time intervals is 
                       provided. The FIR filter applied to the temperature data is longer
                       than the one applied to the MAG data so there is a roughly two
                       hour gap in the temperature data whenever the IFG powers on (i.e.
                       following a spacecraft safing or PAE reset). The value in this column
                       is used for the MAG calibration since it is available for all samples.

parameters.name: SensorT
parameters.description:
IFG sensor temperature [deg C] computed from the value 
                    	 of IFGT_DN in order to provide a comparison with the
                    	 model sensor temperature.

parameters.name: modelET
parameters.description:
The actual IFG electronics temperature (ET) is only available a few times
                       per SOL. Since a value is required for every IFG vector for calibration
                       purposes, a spline fit to the PAE temperature T-0014 is used as a 
                       proxy. T-0014 is sometimes available every minute or so, but is only
                       infrequently returned at night. The observed values of T-0014 are spline
                       fit to produce data set that is sampled at 5 minute resolution or better
                       and then the values between those samples are derived by linear interpolation.
                    	 This value is given in units of degrees Celsius.

parameters.name: T0014
parameters.description:
PDDU AAC (analog acquisition card) AIP (analog input passive) channel 14.  PAE temperature.
                    	 This channel measures the temperature of the PAE electronics box and is used as modeled a proxy
                    	 for the IFG sensor temperature.

parameters.name: EleTemp
parameters.description:
This column contains the actual measured IFG electronics temperature values that are
                    	 recieved in the housekeeping data that come down very infrequently in APID 95. A 
                    	 flight software update on 2019-11-08 increased the downlink frequency of this packet
                    	 to every 1000 seconds.

parameters.name: modelSA
parameters.description:
MLST and UTC dependent model of the fixed solar array current [A]
                    	 derived from the values of the E-0771 from selected time intervals.

parameters.name: E0771
parameters.description: The value of the fixed solar array current [A] in channel E-0771.

parameters.name: modSACT
parameters.description:
MLST and UTC dependent model of the solar array current [A] total (SACT)
                    	derived from the sum of E-0772 and E-0772 from selected time intervals.

parameters.name: SACT
parameters.description: The solar array current [A] total (SACT) computed from the sum of E-0772 and E-0972.
